cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on edge-caching wireless networks and their performance analysis. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a coded caching strategy and derives required backhaul and access rates. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses system energy efficiency and optimization of precoding vectors. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with content delivery time optimization. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with distributed caching in edge networks.
